[[span class="bt"]]SPECIAL CONTAINMENT PROCEDURES:[[/span]] SCP-7000 is maintained via annual performance of the //Ritual of Absolution// (Ritual-7000). Ritual-7000 must be performed exactly once each year, as further detailed in this document.

If Ritual-7000 is performed unsuccessfully, the Foundation must act according to Level Gamma emergency procedures until the next year arrives.

Due to its deep connection to the Foundation[[span class="fnnum"]].[[/span]][[span class="fncon"]] **Radix:** Item has been integrated into the Foundation's command structure. [[/span]], information regarding SCP-7000 and Ritual-7000 must be kept secret. Groups of Interest external to the Foundation learning of SCP-7000 is considered a failure of the Veil Protocol.

In the event that Ritual-7000 loses potence, Foundation thaumatologists are to be employed in order to engineer a new, successful variant of it as soon as is possible.

The date presently dedicated to the completion of Ritual-7000 is August 1st.

[[/div]]

= @@@@

[[div class="blockquote" style="margin: auto;"]]

[[span class="bt"]]DESCRIPTION:[[/span]] SCP-7000 is a powerful thaumaturgical bond which closely links the SCP Foundation to three conceptual entities existing outside of normative reality, maintained and strengthened by the //Ritual of Absolution//.

These three entities -- classically referred to as the //Triad of Absolutes// (or: the //Triad//; the //Absolutes//) -- collectively exert a formidable, generalized influence on the day-to-day affairs and activities of the Foundation at large; this extends to the following areas:

[[div style="display: flex; justify-content: center;"]]
[[div class="blockquote lightweight" style="box-shadow: none; background: #0f5717; border: groove 3px var(--accentColor); display: inline-flex; flex-direction: row; margin: auto; justify-content: center;"]]
[[div]]

* Containment efforts
* Ritualistic practices
* Thaumaturgical practices
* Parascientific innovation
* Strategic practices

[[/div]]

[[div]]

* Bureaucratic processes
* Internal and external security
* Defensive practices
@@ @@ @@ @@ @@ @@ and more.

[[/div]]
[[/div]]
[[/div]]

The influence exerted on the above areas of Foundation activity is, of great note, wholly positive -- while a sufficient relationship between the Foundation and the //Triad// is maintained through Ritual-7000, the Foundation's efforts will, seemingly by chance, yield fruitful results. 

Though both SCP-7000's and the //Triad's// full history with the Foundation is not known, it is understood that this bond is one that has acted as a longstanding boon for almost the totality of our organization's existence. While SCP-7000 is maintained, the Foundation flourishes. It is presumed that the bond's presence is responsible for propelling the Foundation to the grandiose logistical successes it knows today.

If Ritual-7000 is not performed during a given year, or fails, SCP-7000's positive effects will begin to diminish; this progresses on an annual basis for an unknown duration, presumably ending with the bond's total severance. According to record, this has never occurred.

It is not known what such an event entails.

[[/div]]

[[div_ class="fancyhr"]]
